[
    {
        "content": "<p>So Functional Programming in Lean mentions <code>lean --run</code>, then takes you through setting up and building a lake project. But is there a way to just compile a single file into a binary?</p>",
        "id": 425000225,
        "sender_full_name": "James Sully",
        "timestamp": 1709696551
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>lean hello.lean</code> seems to do nothing, and I don't see any relevant flags under <code>lean --help</code></p>",
        "id": 425000387,
        "sender_full_name": "James Sully",
        "timestamp": 1709696654
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>This works</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">lean</span> <span class=\"n\">hello_world.lean</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">c</span> <span class=\"n\">hello_world.c</span> <span class=\"bp\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"n\">leanc</span> <span class=\"n\">hello_world.c</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">o</span> <span class=\"n\">hello_world</span> <span class=\"bp\">&amp;&amp;</span> <span class=\"bp\">./</span><span class=\"n\">hello_world</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>for <code>hello_world.lean</code> file:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">def</span> <span class=\"n\">main</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">IO</span> <span class=\"n\">Unit</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"k\">do</span>\n  <span class=\"n\">IO.println</span> <span class=\"s2\">\"Hello World\"</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p><code>leanc</code> is just a wrapper around <code>clang</code> with the correct flags</p>",
        "id": 425001131,
        "sender_full_name": "Tomas Skrivan",
        "timestamp": 1709697132
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks! I guess this is not the intended workflow lol</p>",
